message.content: cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM. The paper focuses on developing and understanding video models through fill-in-the-blank question-answering, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning), and explores the relative importance of language, static visual features, and moving visual features, which relates to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper presents a dataset for video understanding, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia).
